# Cisco-Spark-BOT
Cisco Spark bot using cisco spark API and Node.js
Step 1: Create a Bot account
Log in at “Spark for Developers” and open the "My Apps" menu.
pick the email "xyz@sparkbot.io"
pick the Cisco Spark Bot access token
Step 2: Run a bot on your VM
git clone https://github.com/budaraju/Cisco-Spark-BOT/
cd Cisco-Spark-BOT
npm install
DEBUG=sparkbot*,samples* SPARK_TOKEN=<Cisco Spark Bot access token> Cisco-Spark-BOT/helloworld.js
set DEBUG=sparkbot*,samples*
set SPARK_TOKEN=<Cisco Spark Bot access token>
Cisco-Spark-BOT\helloworld.js
Step 3: Expose your Bot to the internet
Cisco Spark is run in the Cloud, it requires your Bot to be reachable via a publicly accessible endpoint.
and which is having HTTPS:// PROTOCALL
for SSL letsencrypt and for local environment you can  LocalTunnel and ngrok
Step 4: Create Webhook events
https://developer.ciscospark.com/webhooks-explained.html
https://developer.ciscospark.com/endpoint-webhooks-post.html
Step 5: Test your Cisco Spark Bot
Create a Room
add your bot to room
Type @<botname>/hello and press Enter.
